cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.MM, cs.SD (ordered from most to least likely)

The paper deals with the problem of aligning multiple versions of a piece of music, which involves techniques from signal processing, machine learning, and information retrieval. The most relevant sub-category is cs.SD (Sound), which covers research on audio and music processing. The paper also involves the use of machine learning techniques for alignment, which falls under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Information retrieval techniques are also used to compare different versions of a piece of music, which is covered by cs.IR (Information Retrieval). The paper also involves the use of multiple versions of a piece of music, which is related to cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper deals with the problem of robustness in alignment, which is related to cs.SD (Sound) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
